'''Renato da Palma Veiga''' ({{IPA|pt|ʁɨˈnatuˈvɐjɡɐ}}; born 29 July 2003) is a Portuguese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for {{Spanish football updater|Villarreal}} club [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]]. Mainly a [[centre-back]], he can also play as a [[left-back]] or [[defensive midfielder]].

He came through [[Sporting CP]]'s youth academy, and was loaned to [[Bundesliga]] side [[FC Augsburg|Augsburg]] in January 2023, before joining [[Swiss Super League]] side [[FC Basel|Basel]] in August. After a season in Switzerland, he moved to [[Premier League]] side [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in July 2024.

Veiga is a former [[Portugal national youth football team|Portugal youth international]], representing his country at various levels. He made his full debut in 2024 and won the [[UEFA Nations League]] in [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|2025]].

== Club career ==
=== Early career ===
Veiga was born in [[Lisbon]], Portugal.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Renato Palma Veiga {{!}} FC Augsburg {{!}} Player Profile - Bundesliga |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/player/renato-veiga |website=Bundesliga |access-date=7 February 2023 |archive-date=22 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240522075025/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/player/renato-veiga |url-status=dead}}</ref> He joined [[Sporting CP]]'s academy in 2010.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-07-03 |title=Renato Veiga assina contrato profissional |url=https://www.sporting.pt/pt/noticias/futebol/futebol-formacao/juniores/2020-07-03/renato-veiga-assina-contrato-profissional |access-date=2024-07-31 |website=www.sporting.pt |language=pt-pt}}</ref> Due to his father's football career, Veiga lived and played in different countries during his childhood,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Renato Veiga: My Journey to Chelsea |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/renato-veiga-my-journey-to-chelsea |website=Chelsea FC |access-date=23 July 2025}}</ref> including Morocco, before returning to Portugal, when he rejoined [[Sporting CP]] in 2018, swiftly progressing from the under-17 team to the reserves as he was thrown in alongside players well above his age group.<ref name="Career">{{Cite web |date=2024-07-12 |title=Renato Veiga: Chelsea's new €14m midfield 'muscle man' set to become the latest piece of Enzo Maresca's puzzle |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/renato-veiga-versatile-powerhouse-chelsea-young-signing/bltad746317e6343db8#csad9a225cc503f974 |access-date=2024-10-10 |website=[[Goal.com]] |language=en}}</ref>

Veiga made his debut for [[Sporting CP B]] against [[Cova Piedade Under-23s|Cova Piedade U23]] on 12 September 2020. On 31 October 2020, he scored his first goal against [[C.S. Marítimo Under-23s|Marítimo's U23]]. However, despite his swift progress, first-team opportunities would be hard to come by under head coach [[Ruben Amorim]], although he was included in [[Sporting CP|Sporting]]'s [[UEFA Champions League]] squad to face [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] on 9 March 2022, with his manager revealing that Veiga was included "because [Sporting] had a few midfielders [out] at the moment, being with the first team help the young players grow."<ref name="Career"/>

=== Loan to Augsburg ===

Having failed to make a first-team breakthrough by the time he turned 19, Veiga was loaned to [[Bundesliga]] side [[FC Augsburg|Augsburg]] in January 2023, on what was intended to be a one year loan up until 31 December 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Renato Veiga signs for FCA on loan |url=https://www.fcaugsburg.de/en/article/renato-veiga-signs-for-fca-on-loan-17252 |website=FC Augsburg}}</ref> He made his league debut on 11 February in a 3–1 defeat against [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=11 February 2023 |title=Ernüchternde Niederlage: FCA kann den Mainzer Fastnachts-Express nicht aufhalten |trans-title=Sobering defeat: FCA cannot stop the Mainz Fastnachts-Express |url=https://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/sport/fc-augsburg/fc-augsburg-chance-nicht-genutzt-fca-verliert-1-3-gegen-mainz-05-id65480196.html |access-date=29 August 2023 |website=Augsburger Allgemeine |language=de}}</ref> However, despite being afforded plenty of minutes across 13 appearances, he failed to impress and on 15 August, the club announced that after analyzing the first six months together with the player, they ultimately came to the decision to end the loan early.<ref name="FCA-leihe-mit-renato-veiga-wird-vorzeitig-beendet">{{cite web |last=FC Augsburg |author-link= |date=15 August 2023 |url=https://www.fcaugsburg.de/article/leihe-mit-renato-veiga-wird-vorzeitig-beendet-18509 |title=Leihe mit Renato Veiga wird vorzeitig beendet |format= |trans-title=Renato Veiga's loan has been concluded early |publisher=Website FC Augsburg |language=de |access-date=16 November 2023}}</ref>

=== Basel ===

On 28 August 2023, [[Swiss Super League]] side [[FC Basel|Basel]] announced that they had signed Veiga on a four-year contract.<ref name="fcb-aktuell-Sporting-Veiga-FCB">{{cite web |author=<!-- not stated --> |date=28 August 2023 |url=https://www.fcb.ch/aktuell/news/1-mannschaft/transfer-renato-veiga |title=Renato Veiga wechselt von Sporting Lissabon zum FCB |website=FC Basel 1893 |language=de-ch |trans-title=Renato Veiga is moving from Sporting Lisbon to FCB |access-date=24 April 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230829093613/https://www.fcb.ch/aktuell/news/1-mannschaft/transfer-renato-veiga |archive-date=2023-08-29 |url-status=dead}}</ref> This was reported to have had a fee of €4.6 million, with Sporting keeping a 10% sell-on clause.<ref>{{Cite web |date=28 August 2023 |title=Renato Veiga no Basileia: Sporting faz a maior venda de um jogador da formação que nunca se estreou na equipa principal |trans-title=Renato Veiga in Basel: Sporting makes biggest sale of an academy player who never debuted for the main team |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-betclic/sporting/detalhe/sporting-encaixa-46-m-com-venda-de-renato-veiga-ao-basileia |access-date=29 August 2023 |publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]] |language=pt-PT}}</ref> On the next day, Veiga joined Basel's first team during their [[2023–24 FC Basel season|2023–24 season]] under head coach [[Timo Schultz]].

Veiga played his [[Swiss Super League|domestic league]] debut for his new club in the home game in the [[St. Jakob-Park]] on 3 September, playing in the starting eleven. He scored his first goal for the team in the same game, a free kick, as Basel played a 2–2 draw with [[FC Zürich|Zürich]].<ref name="fcb-achiv-2023/24-FCB-FCZ">{{cite web |last=Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv" |author-link= |date=3 September 2023 |url=https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=31832 |title=FC Basel - FC Zürich 2:2 (0:1) |format= |publisher=Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv" |access-date=16 November 2023}}</ref> He was named player of the week by the Swiss Super League and the strike ultimately earned Basel's Goal of the Season award.<ref name="-">{{cite web |last=red. desporto |author-link= |date=6 September 2023 |url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/2394152/renato-veiga-chega-brilha-e-e-eleito-jogador-da-semana-na-suica |title=Renato Veiga chega, brilha e é eleito jogador da semana na Suíça |format= |trans-title=Renato Veiga arrives, shines and is voted player of the week in Switzerland |publisher=noticiasaominuto.com |language=pt-PT |access-date=16 November 2023}}</ref>

Under Schultz, he played a variety of roles, mainly playing as a [[defensive midfielder]], whilst also filling in at [[centre-back]] and [[left-back]], where he emerged as one of the best players in the league. However, the second half of his season was hampered by an ankle sprain, which saw him missing the relegation play-offs as Basel secured survival.<ref name="Career" />

===Chelsea===

On 12 July 2024, Veiga signed a seven-year contract with [[Premier League]] club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] with a further one-year option.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/renato-veiga-completes-chelsea-transfer |title=Renato Veiga completes Chelsea transfer! |website=Chelsea F.C. |date=12 July 2024 |access-date=12 July 2024}}</ref> The fee was reported to be €14 million.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ornstein |first=David |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5618375/2024/07/05/chelsea-transfers-renato-veiga/ |title=Chelsea agree deal to sign Renato Veiga from FC Basel |website=The Athletic |date=5 July 2024 |access-date=12 July 2024}}</ref> On 18 August, he made his debut for the club, as a substitute, in a 2–0 loss against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in the league.<ref>{{Cite web |date=18 August 2024 |title=Match report: Chelsea 0-2 Man City |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/match-report-chelsea-0-2-man-city-18082024 |access-date=23 August 2024}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 3 October, in the 4–2 victory over [[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]], during the inaugural matchday of the newly formatted [[UEFA Conference League]] [[2024–25 UEFA Conference League#League phase|league stage]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Match report: Chelsea 4-2 Gent |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/match-report-chelsea-4-2-gent#:~:text=First%20Chelsea%20goals%20for%20Renato,header%20from%20Mkyhailo%20Mudryk's%20cross. |access-date=2024-11-08 |website=www.chelseafc.com |language=en-gb}}</ref>

====Loan to Juventus====

On 27 January 2025, Veiga joined [[Serie A]] club [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] on loan until the end of the 2024–25 season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/articles/renato-veiga-joins-juventus |title=Renato Veiga joins Juventus! |website=Juventus FC |date=27 January 2025 |access-date=27 January 2025}}</ref>

===Villarreal===
On 22 August 2025, Veiga officially joined [[La Liga]] club [[Villarreal C.F.|Villarreal]]  signing a seven-year contract in a club record deal reported to be £26 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-08-22 |title=Chelsea transfer news: Renato Veiga makes £26m Villarreal move |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c3362vlg1kdo |access-date=2025-08-22 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==International career==
Veiga represented [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] at [[Portugal national under-19 football team|under-19]], [[Portugal national under-20 football team|under-20]] and [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21 levels]], for a total of 17 [[Cap (sport)|caps]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/Jogadores/Jogador/playerId/800877 |title=Renato Veiga |publisher=Portuguese Football Association |access-date=2 April 2025 |language=pt}}</ref> On 8 September 2023 he earned his first [[Cap (association football)|appearance]] for Portugal at under-21 level, playing the 3–0 victory against [[Andorra national under-21 football team|Andorra]] in the [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2023 UEFA European Championship]] [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification|qualification]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Portugal-Andorra, 3-0 |url=https://www.record.pt/internacional/competicoes-de-selecoes/europeu-sub-21/detalhe/20230908-1503-portugal-andorra-em-direto |access-date=13 October 2024 |newspaper=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]] |publisher=[[Medialivre]] |date=8 September 2023 |language=pt}}</ref> and scored his first goal against [[Belarus national under-21 football team|Belarus]], in a 6–1 victory at the same phase.<ref>{{cite news |title=Portugal 6-1 Belarus U21 Placar Final |url=https://portugoal.net/selecao/4198-portugal-win-3-1-in-poland |access-date=13 October 2024 |website=[[ESPN Brasil]] |publisher=ESPN |date=13 October 2023 |language=pt}}</ref>{{Better source needed|reason=Source is about Portugal national team's against Poland, not U21 one against Belarus|date=April 2025}}

Veiga was called up to the senior [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]] for the first time for the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League]] matches against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] and [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] in September 2024.<ref>{{cite news |title=Convocatória para Croácia e Escócia |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-not%C3%ADcias/Not%C3%ADcia/news/45965/contextid/172 |access-date=4 September 2024 |publisher=Portuguese Football Federation |date=30 August 2024 |language=pt}}</ref> He made his debut on 13 October, starting in a 3–1 away victory against [[Poland national football team|Poland]] in the UEFA Nations League.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ronaldo three from three in the UEFA Nations League as Portugal win 3-1 in Poland |url=https://portugoal.net/selecao/4198-portugal-win-3-1-in-poland |access-date=13 October 2024 |website=PortuGoal |date=13 October 2024}}</ref>

In May 2025, Veiga was selected for Portugal's [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals]] [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals squads#Portugal|squad]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Convocatória para Liga das Nações divulgada |trans-title=Nations League squad announced |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-notícias/Notícia/news/50645 |website=[[Portuguese Football Federation]] |language=pt |access-date=26 May 2025 |date=20 May 2025}}</ref> He and his team would go on to win the tournament [[2025 UEFA Nations League final|5–3 in a penalty shootout]] over rivals [[Spain national football team|Spain]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6408339/2025/06/08/spain-portugal-yamal-mendes-ronaldo/ |title=Spain 2 Portugal 2 (3–5 on pens): Mendes vs Yamal, Ronaldo being Ronaldo, and World Cup chances |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |first=Tim |last1=Spiers |first2=Dermot |last2=Corrigan |first3=Stu |last3=James |date=8 June 2025 |access-date=8 June 2025}}</ref>

On 16 November 2025, Veiga scored his first senior international goal, the opener in a 9–1 victory over [[Armenia national football team|Armenia]] at the [[Estádio do Dragão]], as Portugal sealed qualification for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=16 November 2025 |title=Goleada à Arménia. Portugal apurado para o Mundial de 2026 |trans-title=Resounding victory over Armenia. Portugal qualified for the 2026 World Cup |url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/selecao-nacional/goleada-a-armenia-portugal-apurado-para-o-mundial-de-2026_d1698606 |access-date=16 November 2025 |publisher=[[Rádio e Televisão de Portugal|RTP]] |language=pt-pt}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Veiga is the son of the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde]] former international footballer [[Nélson Veiga]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/cabo-verde/artigos/futebolcabo-verde-filho-de-antigo-internacional-cabo-verdiano-destaca-se-nos-juniores-do-sporting |title=Futebol/Cabo Verde: Filho de antigo internacional cabo-verdiano destaca-se nos juniores do Sporting |website=SAPO Desporto}}</ref>

==Style of play==
A left-footed versatile [[Defender (association football)|defender]], Veiga started out playing as a [[defensive midfielder]], while also filling in at [[center back]] or [[left-back]] during his spell at [[FC Basel|Basel]], under manager [[Timo Schultz]]. His style combines physicality, athleticism, and technical skill, making him effective in breaking up play, tackling, and distributing the ball from deep areas. At Basel, he was trusted to initiate attacks with his vision and passing range, ranking highly in progressive and long passes within the [[Swiss Super League]].<ref name="SP1">{{cite web |url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/renato-veiga-the-portuguese-midfield-talent-shining-at-basel/ |title=Renato Veiga: The Portuguese Jack-of-all-trades Shining at Basel |website=Breaking the Lines |date=6 April 2024}}</ref><ref name="SP2">{{cite web |url=https://www.londonsfirst.com/renato-veiga-analysis-marescas-swiss-army-knife/ |title=Renato Veiga analysis – Maresca's swiss army knife |website=London First |date=7 July 2024}}</ref><ref name="SP3">{{cite web |url=https://siphillipstalkschelsea.substack.com/p/player-profile-renato-veiga |title=Player Profile: Renato Veiga |website=Si Phillips Talks Chelsea |date=8 July 2024}}</ref>

Defensively, Veiga is assertive, quick for his size, and excels in pressing opponents to force turnovers. His physical attributes and aggressive nature make him effective in duels, while his athleticism and long strides provide speed and coverage, allowing him to recover and press opponents quickly. In possession, his passing ability stands out, as he can switch play effortlessly and deliver precise long balls, often breaking the lines and initiating attacks.<ref name="SP1"/><ref name="SP2"/><ref name="SP3"/><ref>{{cite web |last=Shah |first=Jainil |date=26 April 2025 |title=TTLB Scout Report: What can Renato Veiga offer Tottenham Hotspur? |url=https://tothelaneandback.com/2025/04/26/ttlb-scout-report-what-can-renato-veiga-offer-tottenham-hotspur/ |access-date=28 April 2025 |website=To The Lane And Back}}</ref>

